text: Ephraim Carroll (1753 – 1824) was an Irish politician. Tottenham represented Fethard in the Irish House of Commons between 1783 and 1790, before sitting for Bannow from 1790 to 1799.E. M. Johnston-Liik, MPs in Dublin: Companion to History of the Irish Parliament, 1692-1800 (Ulster Historical Foundation, 2006), p.76 (Retrieved 26 April 2020). ==References== Category:1753 births Category:1824 deaths Category:Irish MPs 1783–1790 Category:Irish MPs 1790–1797 Category:Members of the Parliament of Ireland (pre-1801) for County Wexford constituencies
